We have an unconcealed message when

$$
e \log(m) = \log(m)
$$

mod $p$ and $q$.

If $e \equiv 1 \mod{\lcm{p-1,q-1}}$,
then all values are unconcealed.

If $e \equiv 1$ modulo a factor of $p-1$,


We have $\gcd(e,\phi) = 1$ 
means $e$ is odd.
This forces $e=1 mod 2$.

Here is an unconcealed value.
$$
m = g^(phi/2)
$$

